## **W9D2 — Grammar Tip (Reactions)**
 
*Week 9 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] How to react naturally in casual English 💬
 
In casual English, we use "Oh" and big reaction words to show we're really listening.
 
It's energetic and warm!
 
👂 Big reaction = instant connection
 
Examples:
 
[Voice] "Oh my gosh!" — big surprise, genuine excitement
 
[Voice] "No way!" — disbelief and excitement mixed together
 
[Voice] "That's so cool!" — warm, enthusiastic approval
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> The secret: your reaction comes FIRST — before any words. "Oh my gosh!" before "that's amazing!" It buys you a second to think AND sounds way more natural!
 
[Practice] Your new friend says: "I just found out I got tickets to my favorite band's show!"
 
Write how you would react. Start with a big reaction word!
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント：カジュアルな反応パターン
 
• Oh my gosh! — 「うわ！まじで！」大きな驚き・感動
 
• No way! — 「うそ！まじで？！」興奮した驚き
 
• That's so cool! — 「それめっちゃいい！かっこいい！」
 
>> なぜ大きな反応が大切なの？
 
日本語で「えー！」「うそ！」と言うように、英語では大きな反応が「本当に聞いてるよ」のサインになります。
 
反応が小さいと、興味がないように見えることがあります。
 
よくある間違い：
 
❌ "That is good." （感情が薄い）
 
✅ "Oh my gosh, that's amazing!" （ずっと自然！）
 
📌 声に出して練習しましょう：
 
"Oh my gosh!" → "No way!" → "That's so cool!"
 
感情を込めて言うのがポイントです！
 
**🟢 sample_response**
 
No way, that's so cool! Which show is it?!
 
