## **W10D2 — Grammar Tip (Reactions)**
 
*Week 10 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] Two powerful casual reaction phrases! 💬
 
This week: "No way!" and "Right?!"
 
These phrases do TWO things at once:
 
1. Show you're excited / can't believe it
 
2. Keep the energy going
 
Examples:
 
[Voice] Friend: "I just found out my art got into the gallery!"
 
[Voice] You: "No way! That's incredible!"
 
[Voice] Friend: "This event is so much better than I expected!"
 
[Voice] You: "Right?! I know — it's amazing!"
 
[Voice] Friend: "I can't believe how fast this year went!"
 
[Voice] You: "Right?! Same! It feels like January was yesterday!"
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> These phrases work like magnets — they pull the other person to keep talking and show you're fully in the moment with them. That's the magic!
 
[Practice] Write a reaction using "No way!" or "Right?!" for this:
 
Your friend says: "I've been baking every weekend and I'm actually getting really good at it!"
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント：
 
• No way! — 「うそ！まじで？！」驚きと興奮を表す
 
• Right?! — 「だよね！？」強い同意・共感（日本語の「だよね！そうそう！」）
 
• Got into the gallery — ギャラリーに作品が選ばれた
 
• I can't believe — 信じられない
 
>> なぜこの2つのフレーズがそんなに便利なの？
 
「No way!」や「Right?!」は一言で2つのことを伝えます：
 
①「それは驚いた！」→ 相手の話に反応している
 
②「もっと聞きたい！」→ 会話を続けるサインを送っている
 
使う場面：
 
• 友達のニュースに驚いたとき → "No way!"
 
• 友達の言葉に全力で同意するとき → "Right?!"
 
📌 声に出して練習：「No way!」「Right?!」— 感情を込めて！
 
