## **W11D2 — Grammar Tip (Follow-up questions)**
 
*Week 11 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] Ask better follow-up questions! 💬
 
You already know how to react — "Oh my gosh!"
 
Now let's make those questions more specific.
 
This week: follow-up question forms for casual conversation
 
[Voice] "Tell me everything!" — I want to hear all the details
 
[Voice] "What was it like?" — how did it feel / what was the experience?
 
[Voice] "Who did you go with?" — was it with people or solo?
 
Examples:
 
Friend: "I went to a rooftop party last weekend!"
 
You: "Oh my gosh! What was it like?!"
 
Friend: "I did a cooking class this week!"
 
You: "No way! Tell me everything — what did you make?"
 
Friend: "I went to a festival in the countryside!"
 
You: "That's so cool! Who did you go with?"
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> The formula: React first → then ask "what," "how," or "who" to get the full story!
 
[Practice] Your friend says: "I spent the weekend at a music festival!"
 
React and ask a follow-up question!
 
**🟡 prompt_text_japanese**
 
📚 文法ポイント（カジュアルな質問形）：
 
• Tell me everything! → 「全部教えて！」
 
  → 詳しく知りたいときの自然なカジュアル表現
 
• What was it like? → 「どんな感じだった？」
 
  → 体験や感想を聞くとき
 
• Who did you go with? → 「誰と行ったの？」
 
  → 一人か、友達と一緒かを聞くとき
 
• Rooftop party — 屋上パーティー
 
• Cooking class — 料理クラス
 
• Festival — フェスティバル（音楽・食べ物など）
 
>> C1との大きな違いは？
 
「How about you?」= 「あなたはどう？」→ 話題が自分に移る
 
「Tell me everything!」= 「全部教えて！」→ 相手の話を続けさせる
 
これがCompetency 1（はじめの一歩）とCompetency 2（会話をつなげよう）の大きな違いです！
 
📌 声に出して：「Tell me everything!」「What was it like?」「Who did you go with?」
 
