## **W14D2 — Grammar Tip (Showing genuine interest)**
 
*Week 14 · Day 2 · Tuesday · Grammar Tip · text*
 
**🔵 prompt_text**
 
[Tip] Validate what people say! 💬
 
"That makes sense" is one of the most powerful phrases in casual English.
 
Use it when:
 
[Voice] Someone explains a feeling → "That makes sense that you feel that way."
 
[Voice] Someone shares a decision → "Oh, that makes sense."
 
[Voice] Someone gives you context → "Ah, that makes total sense."
 
More phrases to show you really get it:
 
[Voice] "I can imagine." — I can picture how that feels
 
[Voice] "That's understandable." — your reaction is completely reasonable
 
[Voice] "Of course!" — yes, that follows naturally
 
Try saying each example out loud before writing!
 
>> The difference between hearing and understanding:
 
Hearing = you received the words
 
Understanding = you show the person their words actually landed
 
"That makes sense" is how you prove you understood.
 
[Practice] Your friend says: "I've been a bit quiet lately — I'm going through some stuff with my family."
 
